## Plugin Structure

### File Organization

```
src/equicordplugins/<pluginName>/
├── index.tsx              # Main plugin file
├── components/            # React components (optional)
│   └── ComponentName.tsx
├── utils/                 # Utility functions (optional)
│   └── helper.ts
└── style.css              # Stylesheet (optional)
```

**Rules:**
- Plugins **must** live in `src/equicordplugins/<pluginName>/`
- Keep the plugin surface small: prefer `index.tsx` + optional `components/` + optional `utils/` + optional `style.css`
- Do not create unnecessary subdirectories
- Group related functionality in the same file when possible

### Plugin Definition

```typescript
export default definePlugin({
    name: "PluginName",
    description: "Clear, concise description of what the plugin does",
    authors: [Devs.Ven, EquicordDevs.YourName],
    dependencies: ["RequiredPlugin"], // Optional
    settings, // Optional
    patches: [ /* ... */ ],
    contextMenus: { /* ... */ },
    start() { /* ... */ },
    stop() { /* ... */ },
});
```

**Rules:**
- Use descriptive names that clearly indicate functionality
- List all contributors in `authors`
- Declare dependencies if your plugin requires other plugins
- Keep descriptions concise but informative

