## Using Existing APIs & Utilities

**CRITICAL**: Always use existing APIs and utilities instead of creating custom implementations.

### Reference Rulesets

For detailed usage, refer to these specialized rulesets:

1. **`@api` Ruleset** (`.cursor/rules/api-ruleset.mdc`)
   - Plugin registration APIs (Commands, Badges, ContextMenu)
   - UI extension APIs (ChatButtons, HeaderBar, UserArea, etc.)
   - Event & Message APIs
   - Storage & Settings APIs
   - Style & Theme APIs
   - Notification & Audio APIs

2. **`@utils` Ruleset** (`.cursor/rules/ruleset.mdc`)
   - Core utilities (Logger, React hooks, lazy loading)
   - Discord-specific utilities
   - Modal, clipboard, CSS, text utilities
   - Type guards, queues, and more

3. **`@components` Ruleset** (`.cursor/rules/components-ruleset.mdc`)
   - ErrorBoundary, Button, Card, Text components
   - Form components, Layout components
   - Margin utilities and more

4. **`@webpack` Ruleset** (`.cursor/rules/webpack-ruleset.mdc`)
   - Module finding utilities
   - Discord components, stores, utilities
   - React integration, menu components

### Quick Reference

```typescript
// ✅ DO - Use existing APIs
import { Commands } from "@api";
import { DataStore } from "@api/DataStore";
import { Button } from "@components";
import { findByPropsLazy } from "@webpack";
import { Logger, copyWithToast } from "@utils";

// ❌ DON'T - Create custom implementations
// Don't create custom command registration
// Don't use localStorage directly
// Don't create custom button components
// Don't access webpack directly
// Don't create custom logging utilities
```

