## Error Handling

### Error Boundaries

**Always wrap injected components:**
```typescript
import ErrorBoundary from "@components/ErrorBoundary";

export default definePlugin({
    renderComponent(props) {
        return (
            <ErrorBoundary noop>
                <YourComponent {...props} />
            </ErrorBoundary>
        );
    }
});
```

**Options:**
- `noop: true` - Component can fail silently (for non-critical UI)
- `fallback: () => <div>Error message</div>` - Custom error UI
- Default - Shows error boundary UI

### Try-Catch Blocks

**Use for async operations:**
```typescript
async function fetchData() {
    try {
        const data = await RestAPI.get({ url: "/endpoint" });
        return data;
    } catch (e) {
        console.error("Failed to fetch data:", e);
        return null;
    }
}
```

