## Lifecycle Management

### start() Method

**Responsibilities:**
- Subscribe to Flux events (if not using `flux` object)
- Initialize caches
- Set up timers/intervals
- Open WebSocket connections
- Load persisted data

**Example:**
```typescript
start() {
    // Load settings/data
    const savedData = await DataStore.get(KEY) ?? [];
    
    // Subscribe to events
    FluxDispatcher.subscribe("EVENT", handler);
    
    // Initialize state
    cache = new Map();
    
    // Set up timers
    intervalId = setInterval(updateFunction, 1000);
}
```

### stop() Method

**Responsibilities:**
- Unsubscribe from all events
- Clear all timers/intervals
- Close WebSocket connections
- Clear caches
- Revert any injected state

**Example:**
```typescript
stop() {
    // Unsubscribe
    FluxDispatcher.unsubscribe("EVENT", handler);
    
    // Clear timers
    if (intervalId) {
        clearInterval(intervalId);
        intervalId = null;
    }
    
    // Close connections
    if (ws) {
        ws.close();
        ws = null;
    }
    
    // Clear caches
    cache.clear();
}
```

**Critical:** `stop()` must fully revert all changes made in `start()`. The plugin should leave no trace when disabled.

