## Pre-Push Requirements

**CRITICAL**: Before pushing code, you **MUST** run all workflow checks locally to ensure everything passes.

### Required Commands

**Always run before pushing:**
```bash
# Run all tests (includes linting and compilation)
pnpm test

# Build web version to verify compilation
pnpm buildWeb

# Validate plugin structure
pnpm generatePluginJson
```

### Workflow Checks

The CI workflow (`.github/workflows/test.yml`) runs:
1. `pnpm test` - Full test suite (linting + compilation)
2. `pnpm buildWeb` - Web version compilation
3. `pnpm generatePluginJson` - Plugin structure validation

**If any of these fail locally, DO NOT push.** Fix the issues first.

### Additional Useful Commands

```bash
pnpm lint        # Linting only
pnpm lint:fix    # Auto-fix linting issues
pnpm testTsc     # TypeScript check only
pnpm lint-styles # CSS linting
```

