## Code Quality Checklist

### Before Pushing

- [ ] **Used existing APIs** - Checked `@api`, `@utils`, `@components`, `@webpack` rulesets
- [ ] **No DOM access** - No `querySelector`, `getElementById`, etc.
- [ ] **No observers** - No `MutationObserver`, `ResizeObserver`, `IntersectionObserver`
- [ ] **No inline layout styles** - Used `className` + CSS
- [ ] **Managed CSS** - Not manually enabled/disabled
- [ ] **Patches consolidated** - Combined related patches when possible
- [ ] **No redundant code** - No duplicate validations or checks
- [ ] **Early validation** - Objects validated before property access
- [ ] **Handlers extracted** - No inline arrow functions with complex logic
- [ ] **Array bounds checked** - Arrays and indices validated before access
- [ ] **Dependencies included** - `useStateFromStores` has proper dependency arrays
- [ ] **Cleanup complete** - `stop()` fully reverts all `start()` changes
- [ ] **All tests pass** - `pnpm test` succeeds
- [ ] **Web builds** - `pnpm buildWeb` succeeds
- [ ] **Plugin structure valid** - `pnpm generatePluginJson` succeeds

### Code Review Readiness

**Your code should be "review-proof":**
- No "why did you do it this way?" changes
- Follow existing Equicord patterns
- Use established APIs and utilities from rulesets
- Avoid fragile UI hooks
- Document non-obvious decisions with comments

